Have you noticed that most YouTubers use the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:05.520
most eye-catching moment from their Shorts as the&nbsp;
thumbnail? That’s because an attractive thumbnail&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:09.600
grabs attention and increases clicks.
But what if your video doesn’t&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:13.280
have a standout moment?
No worries — you can still&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:18.880
create a compelling thumbnail. Just add a catchy&nbsp;
image or visual at the end of your Shorts video,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:24.800
and make it super brief — around 0.3&nbsp;
seconds. When you upload the Short,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:24.800 --> 00:02:29.280
simply select that frame as your thumbnail.
It’s a simple trick that can make a big difference&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:33.600
in grabbing viewers' attention!
When it comes to writing titles for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:38.320
YouTube Shorts, keeping them short&nbsp;
and catchy is key. Here’s a simple&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:38.320 --> 00:02:43.920
strategy to help boost your click-through rate:
Always begin your title with two strong, relevant&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:50.720
keywords. For example, if your video is about a&nbsp;
new iPhone 16 feature, a great title would be:
&nbsp;

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:55.920
IPHONE 16 Hidden Feature.
Why? Because when viewers scroll&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:55.920 --> 00:03:00.400
through YouTube, they often only notice&nbsp;
the first two words of a Shorts title.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:00.400 --> 00:03:05.520
If those words are relevant and eye-catching,&nbsp;
viewers are much more likely to click.
&nbsp;

00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:09.760
There is a pro tips. Write those&nbsp;
first two keywords in ALL capital&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:15.200
letters to grab attention even faster.
Using an emoji at the end of your title can&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:21.200
help your video stand out visually — just make&nbsp;
sure it's related to your content. For example:
&nbsp;

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:26.720
GARDEN HACK That Works.&nbsp;
IPHONE 16 Hidden Feature.
&nbsp;

00:03:26.720 --> 00:03:30.800
Now, it's time to add a hashtag to&nbsp;
your title. Use only hashtag shorts&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:35.520
in your title. It is recommended for both&nbsp;
longer and shorter shorts. And don't use&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:41.440
any other hashtag. Sometimes, if you use more&nbsp;
hashtags, YouTube detects them as spam. 
&nbsp;

00:03:41.440 --> 00:03:48.000
Now when you finish writing your title, don't&nbsp;
publish it. In visibility option keep it unlisted.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:53.200
And then click on the upload shorts button.
 
You might think, “Nobody reads the description of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:57.600
a Shorts video, so I can just leave&nbsp;
it blank.” But that’s a mistake.
&nbsp;

